{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_21","type":"command_execution","command":"\"C:\\\\WINDOWS\\\\System32\\\\WindowsPowerShell\\\\v1.0\\\\powershell.exe\" -Command \"Get-Content -Raw -LiteralPath 'C:\\\\Users\\\\jeffr\\\\Documents\\\\ComfyUI\\\\custom_nodes\\\\otr-model-smoker\\\\baselines\\\\baseline_ltx2.3_dev_t2v_metadata.txt'\"","aggregated_output":"Model: LTX 2.3 22B (dev checkpoint, text-to-video)\nVersion: ltx-2.3-22b-dev (native ComfyUI support)\nMatches loaded weights: checkpoints/ltx-2.3-22b-dev.safetensors, unet/ltx-2.3-22b-dev-Q3_K_M.gguf, unet/ltx-2.3-22b-dev-Q4_K_S.gguf, unet/distilled-1.1/*.gguf, loras/ltxv/ltx2/ltx-2.3-22b-distilled-lora-384-1.1.safetensors, vae/ltx-2.3-22b-dev_video_vae.safetensors + _audio_vae.safetensors, text_encoders/ltx-2.3-22b-dev_embeddings_connectors.safetensors\nOfficial Source: https://docs.comfy.org/tutorials/video/ltx/ltx-2-3\nDirect JSON: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Comfy-Org/workflow_templates/refs/heads/main/templates/video_ltx2_3_t2v.json\nFetched: 2026-06-30\nNode Count (top-level graph): 3 (SaveVideo, MarkdownNote, and a single Subgraph node)\nActual Node Count (inside subgraph \"Text to Video (LTX-2.3)\"): 51\nWorkflow Type: Text-to-Video (audio+video, 22B dev model)\nQuality Notes: This is a completely different, much larger generation (LTX 2.3, 22B params) than the LTX 2b v0.9 already baselined (baseline_ltx_2b_v0.9.json) -- both are present on disk. The official ComfyUI template for LTX-2.3 uses ComfyUI's newer \"subgraph\" nodes-2.0 feature, so the top-level workflow JSON only shows 3 nodes; the real ~51-node pipeline (CLIP/T5, VAE encode/decode, dual video+audio VAE, latent upscaler, sampler cascade) lives nested under definitions.subgraphs. Do not judge complexity by the top-level node count alone.\nKnown Limitations: Requires gemma_3_12B_it text encoder (not T5) -- a much heavier text encoder than LTX 0.9's t5xxl. fp8 checkpoint variant also available for lower VRAM.\n\nDOES NOT FIT A SINGLE RTX 5080 (16GB) AS-IS: checkpoints/ltx-2.3-22b-dev.safetensors on disk is 46.1GB (confirmed via file size, matches 22B params at bf16). Loading this checkpoint alone requires ~44-46GB VRAM, nearly 3x the 5080's 16GB budget. This was caught by kibitz round-1 panel review (Antigravity/Gemini) 2026-06-30 and confirmed against the actual file size.\nFor an actual 5080-appropriate LTX 2.3 run, use the GGUF-quantized variants already on disk instead: unet/ltx-2.3-22b-dev-Q3_K_M.gguf or unet/ltx-2.3-22b-dev-Q4_K_S.gguf (via UnetLoaderGGUF from ComfyUI-GGUF), or the distilled-1.1 GGUF variants under unet/distilled-1.1/. This baseline JSON as fetched loads the full bf16 checkpoint and would need its UNETLoader/CheckpointLoader node swapped to a GGUF loader node pointing at one of those quantized files before it's actually runnable on this hardware.\nVerified: NO ƒ?\" pending load test in ComfyUI (Phase 3, next window). Additionally pending: rebuild/adjust this workflow to use the GGUF loader path above before attempting to run it on the 5080.\n\r\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
